title: Grateful Dead Live at Cameron Indoor Stadium on 1978-04-12
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Dire Wolf, Beat It On Down The Line, Peggy-O, Mama Tried > Mexicali Blues, Finiculi Finicula, Row Jimmy, Minglewood Blues, Loser, Lazy Lightning > Supplication

Set 2

Bertha > Good Lovin', It Must Have Been The Roses, Estimated Prophet > Eyes Of The World > Drums > Truckin' > Wharf Rat > Around & Around

E: U.S. Blues

Duke University

reviews.review_text: This Is It What a tasty sounding recording.    Just one of those Gems that’s too far down the list for the masses to check out.  Nice Separation and great definition.     Thank you for this gift.   This one gets a whole lotta lumps!

Loser! Great show, great era. Keith still with some vitality, Jerry's voice still strong, the band enjoys pushing it to eleven as often as possible.  Check out the Loser and turn it up loud.  What a band, holy smokes.
Agree with the other reviewer.... Loser of all Losers!
